==English==
===Etymology===
Part translation of Dutch ''[[verloren]] [[hoop#Dutch|hoop]]'' ‘lost troop’ (compare English ''[[forlese]]'', ''[[heap]]'').

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/fəˌlɔ:nˈhəʊp/}}

===Noun phrase===
{{en-noun|sg=[[forlorn]] [[hope]]}}

# {{military}} A small troop picked to make an advance attack, or the first attack; a storming party.
# Any dangerous or hopeless venture.